    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi @sadamameer, in order to do that you need to implement two things. One is a [transformData](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/widgets-common-api.html#transformdata), that will let you process your floats into elements that can be used in the the template. You can find an example for the [transformData of a star rating here](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/e78de702ed53798431493df6e966a53d749930d7/docgen/src/examples/media/search.js#L44-L50). The other is the template. You can find the star rating template a [little above the transform](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/e78de702ed53798431493df6e966a53d749930d7/docgen/src/examples/media/search.js#L28) data.\r\n\r\nJust as a side note, the issues in this project are for bug reports or feature proposal. Only opening issues for bugs or features really helps us maintain a good quality on the project.\r\n\r\nIf you're looking for support, we suggest that you go through the [Algolia community forum](https://discourse.algolia.com/) or [stack overflow](https://stackoverflow.com/tags/instantsearch.js/). We try to be reactive on those two platforms and  Thanks for using InstantSearch.js and Algolia ❤️ ",
